Thanks,
I have been working with JUnitPP for the property mechanism.
Indeed they have something for running tests with repetitions and invocation
delays: java junit.extensions.PPTestRunner. I haven&#39;t found the time to try
it out.

One other remark about JUnitPP: I used their ConfigurableTestCase. It worked
well in a stand-alone environment, but in a server based environment (in
combination with JUnitEE) it stopped the application server because of
System.exit calls in their code. I informed the authors but got no feedback
so far.
Instead I wrote something similar and called it ConfiguredTestCase but it is
far less functional than ConfigurableTestCase, but at least it doesn&#39;t bring
the application server down.
Just FYI.

Kind regards,

Dirk

